More information :

Triple arched bridge over the Sella river, Cangas de Onis, Asturias, Spain. The bridge is known locally as the Roman bridge. Although it was built over a much earlier structure, this bridge dates from the 13th century. The cross hanging from the keystone of the central arch is the Cross of Victory, or Cruz de la Victoria, the symbol of Asturias.
